history.text: Hi.
Hey...so, have you ever seen Zootopia before?
No what is it about?

Basically it's an animated film where the premise is that a small town Bunny fulfills her dream of becoming a cop in the big city but it doesn't necessarily go as planned because she is assigned as a parking maid. She eventually pairs up with this con artist Fox and they stumble upon a big crime dilemma.
Has an all star cast
And a 98%rotten tomatoes rating
Zootopia sounds like a fun movie. Especially for kids. I take it is a cartoon?
Yes, it's awesome for kids, but it's also really entertaining for adults. The kids will love all of the animal characters and the adults will enjoy the plot.
Do you have kids?
I will have to get my family to watch it. I wonder if I can download it on Amazon.
Have you seen it?
Rotten tomatoes is a reliable website.
I have seen it, it's awesome! Jason Bateman plays the fox and I think he is terrific.
The family will love all of the characters. And it's funny!
A meter maid bunny. Somebody had a funny idea.
98 percent is a really high rating.
Jason Bateman is a good actor. Who else is in it?
Absolutely. The fox is a "con artist" and the Otter is the bad guy. The police chief is a Water Buffalo.
Idris Elba and Ginnifer Goodwin
Oh I liked Ginnifer Goodwin.
Yea 98% is great, 8/10 on IMDB as well.
I wonder why only 8 out of ten there? Somebody was tough on them.
I don't want to give too  much of the plot away for you
I appreciate that.
What year did it come out?
Yea, probably. People can be huge critics. But if you generally enjoy movies, especially Pixar movies and whatnot I am confident you will enjoy this one.
It came out in 2016
Pixar is always awesome. I am surprised I missed this one.
Thanks for the info.
Absolutely. Anything else you want to know about it?
No it sounds like something we will rent this weekend.
Awesome, glad I could be of help to you. I really think you and your family will enjoy this one. Get the popcorn ready.
Lol. Have a good day.

uid1response.feedback: The chatbot was very helpful and seemed human and got me interested in seeing the movie.
